&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;SS-0101 Clinical Resourcing Lead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role attracts an annual salary of £45,000 (£21.57 per hour).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Devon Doctors Group are recruiting for an experienced Resourcing Lead to develop talent pipelines for critical clinical roles within the organisation across Devon and Somerset. The successful candidate will have experience of engaging internal stakeholders at director level to ascertain the requirement and be able to craft and deliver on effective resourcing strategies for each role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience of engaging with Clinical Commissioning Groups is vital, in addition to an understanding of the role they play in supporting clinical resourcing across our footprint.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will be based in Exeter, but with flexibility to undertake this from a remote location for the right candidate within Devon and Somerset.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further details of the role are provided in the Job Description.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Devon Doctors has been delivering urgent primary care in Devon to an exceptional standard for over twenty years.  Currently with the Integrated Urgent Care Service (IUCS) for Devon, Integrated Urgent Care Service (IUCS) Somerset. Our sister companies include Access Health and Access Dental who offer a range of dentistry and primary care services across the Peninsula.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits of working for us include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;27 days holiday (plus Bank Holidays)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Paid Volunteering day per year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounts at retailers via Perkbox&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Free 24 hour Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to being an inclusive employer with a diverse workforce. We encourage applications from people from all backgrounds, cultures and experiences to contribute to the diversity of our organisation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date:                                       18/11/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Proposed Interview date:                TBC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
